    <stitle>5 SPEED AND 6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON SERIES - ASSEMBLE - COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLY (FS-5205)</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="5">
        <title>COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLY (FS-5205)</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Do not heat the bearings above 275&#176;F (136&#176;C). If possible, use a heat lamp as the
                    source.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align 4th gear keyway with the shaft key, long hub to the shaft front, and position the gear
                and shaft in the press (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026d3">Figure 133</hotlnk>). Press 4th gear into place.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13026d3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13026d3" filename="../figg13/G13026D3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 133. Align 4th Gear Keyway With Shaft Key</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align drive gear keyway with the shaft key, long hub to the shaft rear, and position the
                gear and shaft in the press (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026d4">Figure 134</hotlnk>). Press the drive gear into place.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13026d4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13026d4" filename="../figg13/G13026D4.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 134. Align Drive Gear Keyway With Shaft Key</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the drive gear retaining snap ring in the groove (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026d5">Figure 135</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13026d5" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13026d5" filename="../figg13/G13026D5.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 135. Install Drive Gear Retaining Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Heat and install the front countershaft bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026d6">Figure 136</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13026d6" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13026d6" filename="../figg13/G13026D6.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 136. Heat and Install Front Countershaft Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If removed, heat and install the rear countershaft bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026d7">Figure 137</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13026d7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13026d7" filename="../figg13/G13026D7.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 137. Heat and Install Rear Countershaft Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
